neCombinationSingleWeights_apply_self","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L653-L654","name":"Finset.affineCombinationSingleWeights","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombinationSingleWeights","doc":"Weights for expressing a single point as an affine combination. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L638-L647","name":"Finset.map_affineCombination","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.map_affineCombination","doc":"Affine maps commute with affine combinations. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L625-L632","name":"Finset.eq_affineCombination_subset_iff_eq_affineCombination_subtype","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.eq_affineCombination_subset_iff_eq_affineCombination_subtype","doc":"Suppose an indexed family of points is given, along with a subset\nof the index type.  A point can be expressed as an\n`affineCombination` using a `Finset` lying within that subset and\nwith sum of weights 1 if and only if it can be expressed an\n`affineCombination` with sum of weights 1 for the corresponding\nindexed family whose index type is the subtype corresponding to that\nsubset. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L608-L613","name":"Finset.eq_weightedVSub_subset_iff_eq_weightedVSub_subtype","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.eq_weightedVSub_subset_iff_eq_weightedVSub_subtype","doc":"Suppose an indexed family of points is given, along with a subset\nof the index type.  A vector can be expressed as `weightedVSub` using\na `Finset` lying within that subset and with sum of weights 0 if and\nonly if it can be expressed as `weightedVSub` with sum of weights 0\nfor the corresponding indexed family whose index type is the subtype\ncorresponding to that subset. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L582-L597","name":"Finset.eq_weightedVSubOfPoint_subset_iff_eq_weightedVSubOfPoint_subtype","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.eq_weightedVSubOfPoint_subset_iff_eq_weightedVSubOfPoint_subtype","doc":"Suppose an indexed family of points is given, along with a subset\nof the index type.  A vector can be expressed as\n`weightedVSubOfPoint` using a `Finset` lying within that subset and\nwith a given sum of weights if and only if it can be expressed as\n`weightedVSubOfPoint` with that sum of weights for the\ncorresponding indexed family whose index type is the subtype\ncorresponding to that subset. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L568-L572","name":"Finset.affineCombination_filter_of_ne","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_filter_of_ne","doc":"An affine combination over `s.filter pred` equals one over `s` if all the weights at indices\nin `s` not satisfying `pred` are zero. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L559-L563","name":"Finset.affineCombination_subtype_eq_filter","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_subtype_eq_filter","doc":"An affine combination over `s.subtype pred` equals one over `s.filter pred`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L545-L555","name":"Finset.affineCombination_eq_of_weightedVSub_eq_zero_of_eq_neg_one","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_eq_of_weightedVSub_eq_zero_of_eq_neg_one","doc":"If a weighted sum is zero and one of the weights is `-1`, the corresponding point is\nthe affine combination of the other points with the given weights. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L536-L540","name":"Finset.affineCombination_sdiff_sub","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_sdiff_sub","doc":"A weighted sum may be split into a subtraction of affine combinations over two subsets. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L530-L532","name":"Finset.sum_smul_const_vsub_eq_vsub_affineCombination","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.sum_smul_const_vsub_eq_vsub_affineCombination","doc":"A weighted sum of pairwise subtractions, where the point on the left is constant and the\nsum of the weights is 1. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L523-L525","name":"Finset.sum_smul_vsub_const_eq_affineCombination_vsub","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.sum_smul_vsub_const_eq_affineCombination_vsub","doc":"A weighted sum of pairwise subtractions, where the point on the right is constant and the\nsum of the weights is 1. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L514-L518","name":"Finset.sum_smul_vsub_eq_affineCombination_vsub","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.sum_smul_vsub_eq_affineCombination_vsub","doc":"A weighted sum of pairwise subtractions, expressed as a subtraction of two `affineCombination`\nexpressions. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L507-L509","name":"Finset.affineCombination_map","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_map","doc":"An affine combination, over the image of an embedding, equals an\naffine combination with the same points and weights over the original\n`Finset`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L497-L501","name":"Finset.affineCombination_indicator_subset","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_indicator_subset","doc":"An affine combination is unaffected by changing the weights to the\ncorresponding indicator function and adding points to the set. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L482-L492","name":"Finset.affineCombination_of_eq_one_of_eq_zero","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_of_eq_one_of_eq_zero","doc":"An `affineCombination` equals a point if that point is in the set\nand has weight 1 and the other points in the set have weight 0. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L474-L476","name":"Finset.affineCombination_eq_linear_combination","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_eq_linear_combination","doc":"Viewing a module as an affine space modelled on itself, affine combinations are just linear\ncombinations. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L466-L468","name":"Finset.weightedVSub_eq_linear_combination","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.weightedVSub_eq_linear_combination","doc":"Viewing a module as an affine space modelled on itself, a `weightedVSub` is just a linear\ncombination. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L457-L460","name":"Finset.attach_affineCombination_coe","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.attach_affineCombination_coe","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L441-L454","name":"Finset.attach_affineCombination_of_injective","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.attach_affineCombination_of_injective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L436-L438","name":"Finset.affineCombination_vsub","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_vsub","doc":"Subtracting two `affineCombination`s. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L430-L432","name":"Finset.weightedVSub_vadd_affineCombination","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.weightedVSub_vadd_affineCombination","doc":"Adding a `weightedVSub` to an `affineCombination`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L423-L426","name":"Finset.affineCombination_eq_weightedVSubOfPoint_vadd_of_sum_eq_one","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_eq_weightedVSubOfPoint_vadd_of_sum_eq_one","doc":"`affineCombination` gives the sum with any base point, when the\nsum of the weights is 1. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L416-L418","name":"Finset.affineCombination_congr","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_congr","doc":"`affineCombination` gives equal results for two families of weights and two families of\npoints that are equal on `s`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L409-L411","name":"Finset.affineCombination_apply_const","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_apply_const","doc":"The value of `affineCombination`, where the given points are equal. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L401-L404","name":"Finset.affineCombination_apply","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_apply","doc":"Applying `affineCombination` with given weights.  This is for the\ncase where a result involving a default base point is OK (for example,\nwhen that base point will cancel out later); a more typical use case\nfor `affineCombination` would involve selecting a preferred base\npoint with\n`affineCombination_eq_weightedVSubOfPoint_vadd_of_sum_eq_one` and\nthen using `weightedVSubOfPoint_apply`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L387-L389","name":"Finset.affineCombination_linear","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination_linear","doc":"The linear map corresponding to `affineCombination` is\n`weightedVSub`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L377-L381","name":"Finset.affineCombination","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.affineCombination","doc":"A weighted sum of the results of subtracting a default base point\nfrom the given points, added to that base point, as an affine map on\nthe weights.  This is intended to be used when the sum of the weights\nis 1, in which case it is an affine combination (barycenter) of the\npoints with the given weights; that condition is specified as a\nhypothesis on those lemmas that require it. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L367-L367","name":"Finset.instAddTorsorForAllAddGroupToAddGroupToAddGroupWithOne","kind":"instance","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.instAddTorsorForAllAddGroupToAddGroupToAddGroupWithOne","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L362-L364","name":"Finset.weightedVSub_const_smul","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.weightedVSub_const_smul","doc":"A constant multiplier of the weights in `weightedVSub_of` may be moved outside the sum. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L356-L358","name":"Finset.weightedVSub_filter_of_ne","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.weightedVSub_filter_of_ne","doc":"A weighted sum over `s.filter pred` equals one over `s` if all the weights at indices in `s`\nnot satisfying `pred` are zero. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L347-L351","name":"Finset.weightedVSub_subtype_eq_filter","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.weightedVSub_subtype_eq_filter","doc":"A weighted sum over `s.subtype pred` equals one over `s.filter pred`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L341-L343","name":"Finset.weightedVSub_sdiff_sub","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.html#Finset.weightedVSub_sdiff_sub","doc":"A weighted sum may be split into a subtraction of such sums over two subsets. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/AffineSpace/Combination.lean#L335-L337","name":"Finset.weightedVSub